According to a new report from Intel Market Research, the global Metal Polishing Buffing Compounds market was valued at USD 80.78 million in 2026 and is projected to reach USD 156 million by 2034, exhibiting a robust CAGR of 10.1% during the forecast period (2025–2034). This growth is propelled by the expanding demand for high‑precision metal finishing across automotive, aerospace, electronics and general manufacturing sectors, the continuous push for advanced manufacturing technologies, and the rising awareness of surface‑treatment efficiency. In addition, innovations such as nano‑enhanced abrasive particles are extending product performance horizons, while key players-including Menzerna, Osborn GmbH, Maverick Abrasives, 3M, Luxor Polishing Compounds and Zéphyr-are actively launching new formulations and widening distribution networks, which further fuels market expansion.
Metal Polishing and Buffing Compounds are specialized materials used to improve the surface quality of metals by refining, smoothing, and creating a high‑gloss or mirror‑like finish. They combine abrasive particles with a binding agent or wax to effectively remove imperfections and enhance the appearance of metal surfaces across automotive, aerospace, electronics and general manufacturing applications.
Metal Polishing Buffing Compounds play an indispensable role in producing components that must meet stringent aesthetic and functional standards. Manufacturers across high‑value industries rely on these compounds to achieve smooth, uniform surfaces that enhance corrosion resistance, optical clarity, and assembly compatibility, thereby shortening production times and reducing waste. Continued investment in precision manufacturing and additive‑manufacturing processes has further elevated the importance of high‑performance polishing solutions.
